Netia SA , Polandâ€™s second-largest
fixed-line phone operator, said it increased a loan to fund
potential acquisitions to 700 million zloty ($243 million).  BNP Paribas SA, Rabobank Polska SA, Raiffeisen Bank Polska
SA and BRE Bank SA provided the financing, which was initially
signed as a 600 million-zloty facility on July 29, Warsaw-based
Netia said in a statement.  Netia now has more than 1 billion zloty to fund future
acquisitions, including more than 300 million zloty of cash,
according to the statement.  Netia climbed 3.2 percent to 5.77 zloty at 10:38 a.m. in
Warsaw, heading for the highest close since January 2006.  To contact the reporter on this story:
